# Generate an array of random integers between 1 and 100
    array = np.random.randint(1, 101, size=ARRAY_SIZE)

    # Calculate the mean and standard deviation
    mean = np.mean(array)
    std = np.std(array)

    # Create a histogram of the distribution
    ax = plt.hist(array, bins=50)
    plt.title("Histogram of Random Integers")
    plt.xlabel("Value")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")

    # Plot the mean as a dashed line
    plt.axvline(mean, color="red", linestyle="--")

    # Plot the standard deviation as dashed lines
    plt.axvline(mean + std, color="purple", linestyle="--")
    plt.axvline(mean - std, color="purple", linestyle="--")

    return array, mean, std, ax
